For detailed naming guidelines per layer, see `doc/NamingGuidelines.md`.
For general project rules, see `.cursor/rules/project-rules.mdc`.

- Adhere clean code architecture layer (domain, application, infrastructure, data access, presentation)
- Name should communicate intent, avoid disinformation, be descriptive
- Domain name should be PascalCase, simple descriptive nouns, plain english
- Application (service) layer follows:
  -- Entity + Action + Service for service interface.
  -- action + Entity + detail for service methods.
  -- Action + Entity + UseCase for service use case.
  -- Use the following application verbs: create, retrieve, update, delete, list, search
- Infrastructure layer follows
  -- Entity + Repository for repository interface.
  -- Data verb + Entity + Detail for repository method.
  -- find/query + Entity + ByCondition for repository query method.
  -- Use the following data verbs: persist, find, query, list, update, remove
- Data Access layer or Adapters follows
  -- Technology + Entity + Adapter for adapter class.
  -- Data verb + Entity + Detail for adapter method.
  -- Database operation for private helpers.
  -- Use the following data verbs: persist, find, query, list, update, remove
